\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b hoppeanum}: Leaves without stellate hairs above. Involucral bracts (8-)11-14 × 2-4 mm, more or less ovate, in the central part with numerous long simple eglandular hairs which are dark at least in their basal half, without or with few glandular hairs; margins pale, without hairs. •{\i  Alps}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b pilisquamum} Naegeli & Peter, {\i Hier. Mittel-Eur.}{\b  1}: 124 (1885): Leaves without stellate hairs above. Involucral bracts 9-12 × 1·5-3 mm, lanceolate or narrowly ovate, with numerous simple eglandular hairs which are pale throughout or dark only at the very base, without or with few glandular hairs; margins not pale, covered with hairs. {\i Throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b testimoniale} Naegeli ex Peter, {\i Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  5}: 251 (1884): Leaves without stellate hairs above. Involucral bracts 10-12 × 1·5-2·5 mm, lanceolate to narrowly ovate, with numerous unequal, dark, broad-based glandular hairs, without or with few simple eglandular hairs; margins not pale, covered with hairs.{\i  C. & S.E. Europe}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b troicum} Zahn in Engler,{\i  Pflanzenreich}{\b  82}({\b IV.280}): 1153 (1923): Leaves without stellate hairs above. Involucral bracts 6-10 × 1·3-2 mm, more or less lanceolate, with numerous short glandular hairs which are dark only,at the base, without or with few simple eglandular hairs; margins rarely pale, usually covered with stellate hairs.{\i  Balkan peninsula and E.C. Europe, extending to N. Italy}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b e}) Subsp. {\b cilicicum} Naegeli & Peter,{\i  Hier. Mittel-Eur.}{\b  1}: 121 (1885): Leaves with dense stellate hairs above. Involucral bracts 10-11 × 1·5-2 mm, with numerous short glandular hairs, without or with few simple eglandular hairs; margins not pale, with hairs. {\i Bulgaria }({\i E. Stara Planina}).
\par 

\par 

